know that Try to recall how Python interprets the truth of
a condition, and note that these two forms are equivalent: 
(while number != 0: & if number % 2:)


By the way, look at the print() function. The way we've used
it here is called multi-line printing. You can use triple
quotes to print strings on multiple lines in order to make
text easier to read, or create a special text-based design. 